<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HONGKONG-ANNIVERSARY (Hong Kong) _ His hometown is marking the
first anniversary of its return to China on July 1, but Loon
Wai-ting is in no mood to celebrate. Loon has spent the year
without a job. Of course, Britain's exit from Hong Kong has had
little to do with the economic downturn of its former colony, but
Loon speaks for many Hong Kong people, who are being ravaged by
rising unemployment, a 20 percent drop in the stock market, and a
40 percent decline in the property market. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   IRAN-TRIAL (Tehran, Iran) _ In a huge courtroom under the heat
and glare of TV klieg lights, the mayor of Tehran is struggling to
keep his job, clear his name and justify the way he does business.
By Elaine Sciolino.
</P>
<P>
   FRENCH-GENDER (Paris) _ You say ``Madame le ministre,'' I say
``Madame la ministre,'' the French government decreed on Monday.
Let's call the whole thing off, the Academie Francaise thundered on
Tuesday. The French Academy, a male bastion founded by Cardinal
Richelieu in 1635, is positively beside itself about proposals like
making ``ministre,'' which is a masculine noun, feminine when the
minister in question is a woman. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EXCLUSIVE-MCVEIGH (Undated) _ Previously undisclosed letters
written before the Oklahoma City bombing and subsequent FBI
interviews conducted afterward indicate that even though Timothy
McVeigh never confided any plans to his family, he could not hide
his feelings, so much so that his father and sister suspected right
after the 1995 blast that he had been responsible. But the McVeigh
family was divided on the issue of how Timothy McVeigh came to hate
the government so much that he would kill 168 men, women and
children. By Jo Thomas.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AIDS-THERAPY (Geneva) _ Researchers raised the possibility
that treatment may someday eliminate the AIDS virus from the body
or lower it to a point where the immune system can successfully
control it. By Lawrence K. Altman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON _ (Moved in ``w'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIRTHS _ The birth rate for unmarried black women, long a focal
point in the debate over the causes of poverty among blacks, has
reached its lowest point in 40 years, federal health officials say
_ one result of a national survey of birth certificates from all
the states. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
