<SLUG> BC-BBO-DODGERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHEFFIELD WOULD PASS ON ALL-STAR INVITATION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Gary Sheffield will appeal a three-day
suspension handed down Tuesday for his role in Sunday's fight, but
he won't play if selected as a reserve for the July 7 All-Star
Game.
</P>
<P>
   Sheffield, who received five stitches over his left eye after a
bench-clearing brawl with Pittsburgh, learned Tuesday he and
Pirates catcher Jason Kendall each must miss three games. Sheffield
can play until a hearing is arranged, which isn't expected until
mid-July.
</P>
<P>
   Sheffield said the eye injury, a sore lower back and the fact
that he hasn't been home since spring training, rules out any
appearance at the All-Star Game at Coors Field in Denver.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a combination of things,'' said Sheffield, who is batting
.338 in 38 games with the Dodgers and .303 overall. ``I want to
spend time with my family. It has been a long time.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers do not have a clear pick among the reserves, which
will be announced Friday. It probably will go to Raul Mondesi, who
leads the club with 17 homers. Eric Young, who leads the National
League with 32 stolen bases, had an outside shot until re-injuring
his right thigh muscle running out a ground ball Tuesday in the
first inning.
</P>
<P>
   Catcher Charles Johnson is second to Mike Piazza in the voting
and played for NL manager Jim Leyland, but he is batting just .208
after going 0 for 3 Tuesday with two strikeouts.
</P>
<P>
   Sheffield was back in the lineup Tuesday and drove in a run in
the fifth inning. He said the altercation started Sunday when
Kendall started shouting obscenities after a near collision at home
plate. The brawl woke up the Pirates, who trailed by three runs at
the time and went on to score five runs in the final three innings.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't go into that thinking this would give the team a
boost or go the other way,'' Sheffield said. ``Everybody has a job
to do. That shouldn't affect the way you play the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Charges dropped: Raul Mondesi will not faces drunk driving
charges stemming from a June 13 incident when he was pulled over
near his home in Glendale.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi registered a .083 alcohol level, which is legally drunk
in California. But the Glendale district attorney office notified
Mondesi's attorney Miles Berman on Tuesday that charges would not
be filed.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi, benched the day of the incident, said his driving
became erratic after getting separated from friends who were
driving behind him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to thank the district attorney's office that justice
has been done in my case,'' Mondesi said. ``Playing baseball in
America has been the greatest thrill in my life and I am thankful
for the opportunity to play here. I want to thank the fans and
Dodgers who stood by me during this unfortunate incident.''
</P>
<P>
   Martinez lost for year: Dodgers right-hander Ramon Martinez
underwent surgery Tuesday to repair his right shoulder and is not
expected to pitch competitively until the middle of next season.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers orthopedist Frank Jobe repaired the rotator cuff during
the 1{-hour procedure at Centinela Hospital Medical Center in
Inglewood. Jobe, however, said the cartilage damage in the shoulder
was not as serious as first believed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he will come all the way back,'' Jobe said. ``We think
his velocity can be like it was before. He starts rehabbing
tomorrow and we want him to maintain his range of motion and give
the tear time to heal. We know that takes six months to heal down
solid. Then he has to get his strength back. That is why I am
saying a year.''
</P>
<P>
   It is uncertain, however, where Martinez will be in a year. He
is in the final season of a multi-year contract. The Dodgers hold
an option for next year. They could pick up the option for $5.6
million or give him a buyout at $600,000. The club is expected to
exercise the option and re-sign Martinez for a lower figure.
</P>
</TEXT>
