Slackers brand two years ago specifically to meet the needs of male
baby boomers, who are trying to adjust to the casualization and new
dress codes in corporate America. They felt they needed more
options between khakis and suits.
</P>
<P>
   ``The launch has been very successful. The newest ad campaign
will be all about a competitive edge, doing well at work and home,
wanting to be noticed. We chose models in their late 30s _ men who
were not too modely, but nice looking; looks a consumer can relate
to,'' Friedman said. ``We've heard a lot of feedback from women
about doing a line for female baby boomers. That's on the
horizon.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _______ &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Karyn Monget is a reporter for Fairchild Publications.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
