<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Black films lineup
 &HT;    By Diane Holloway
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's the schedule for TCM's ``A Separate Cinema'':
</P>
<P>
   _ July 1Oscar Micheaux Night 7 p.m. ``Midnight Ramble,'' (1994
documentary about race films) 8 p.m. ``The Symbol of the
Unconquered'' (1921) 9 p.m. ``Within Our Gates'' (1920) 10:30 p.m.
``Midnight Ramble,'' repeat 11:30 p.m. ``Swing'' (1938) 1 a.m.
``The Symbol of the Unconquered,'' repeat 2 a.m. ``Scar of Shame''
(1927)
</P>
<P>
   _ July 8 Paul Robeson and Herbert Jeffrey 7 p.m. ``King
Solomon's Mines'' (1937) 8:30 p.m. ``Song of Freedom'' (1936) 9:45
p.m. ``Jericho'' (1937) 11:15 p.m. ``Two Gun Man from Harlem''
(1938) 12:30 a.m. ``The Bronze Buckaroo'' (1938) 1:30 a.m. ``Harlem
Rides the Range'' (1939)
</P>
<P>
   _ July 15 , Josephine Baker and Spencer Williams 7 p.m.
``Princess Tam Tam'' (1935) 8:30 p.m. ``Zou Zou'' (1934) 10:30 p.m.
``Go Down, Death'' (1944) 11:30 p.m. ``The Blood of Jesus'' (1941)
12:30 a.m. ``Dirty Gertie From Harlem'' (1946) 1:45 a.m. ``Juke
Joint'' (1947)
</P>
<P>
   _ July 22, Crime Stories 7 p.m. ``Dark Manhattan'' (1937) 8:20
p.m. ``Mystery in Swing'' (1940) 9:30 p.m. ``Gang War'' (1940)
10:45 p.m. ``Miracle in Harlem'' (1948) 12 a.m. ``Midnight Shadow''
(1939) 1 a.m. ``Midnight Ramble,'' repeat
</P>
<P>
   _ July 29, Sports/Musicals 7 p.m. ``The Jackie Robinson Story''
(1950) 8:30 p.m. ``The Spirit of Youth'' (1937) 9:45 p.m. ``Keep
Punching'' (1939) 11:15 p.m. ``Duke Is Tops'' (1938) 12:30 a.m.
``Broken Strings'' (1940) 1:30 a.m. ``Junction '88'' (1947) 2:45
a.m. ``Sepia Cinderella'' (1947) 4 a.m. ``Boy! What a Girl'' (1946)
</P>
