</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ What have Greg Louganis and Margaret Thatcher
been up to lately? (Bessonnette, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) IN
TWO TAKES. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GREIG-COLUMN _ What does the 10/6 mean on the Mad Hatter's hat
in ``Alice in Wonderland''? Answers from Jane Greig. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e category)
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ Highlights of tomorrow's TV viewing.
ETA: 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BLACKFILMS _ Pioneering black independent filmmakers of the
1920s and '30s countered the demeaning, racist depictions of their
people seen in mainstream films at the time with ``race films''
made especially for black audiences. Turner Classic Movies has
located 29 of these historic classics and will air them on five
consecutive Wednesdays, beginning July 1, under the umbrella title
``A Separate Cinema.'' (Holloway, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BLACKFILMS-LINEUP.
</P>
