<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    'Alice in Wonderland' mystery can drive one Mad
 &HT;    By Jane Greig
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ For copies of Jane's book, ``Thanks for
Asking!'' _ a compilation of more than 600 favorite questions and
answers _ call 288-6291 or (800) 424-6291.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you answer two questions? What does the 10/6 mean on
the Mad Hatter's hat in ``Alice in Wonderland''? What do the words
``Ve Ri Tas'' mean (on a school sweatshirt)? _M. B.
</P>
<P>
   A: It means you did not study Latin; veritas is Latin for truth.
</P>
<P>
   The Mad Hatter's hat sports a card with ``10/6'' on it, which
had me stumped until I contacted the president of the Lewis Carroll
Society of North America. Joel Birenbaum says, ``It stands for the
price, 10 shillings and 6 pence. The hat is for sale.''
</P>
<P>
   Interested in finding out more about Charles Lutwidge Dodgson, a
k a Lewis Carroll? Contact the society at www.lewiscarroll.org or
write Ellie Luchinsky, LCSNA Secretary, 18 Fitzharding Place,
Owings Mill, Md. 21117.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am in the third grade. May I please have Michael Jordan's
address? I would like to tell him that I like him. Thank you. _Sean
Dunn
</P>
<P>
   A: Your good wishes will brighten the Chicago Bulls star's day.
</P>
<P>
   Write to the six-time NBA Finals MVP at his fan club: Jump,
Inc., 676 N. Michigan Ave., Suite 2930, Chicago, Ill. 60611. You
can also e-mail him at jump-inc.com. Don't wait by the mailbox.
Jordan receives about 1,000 letters a week, and perhaps more as
fans (they are legion) aim to persuade the congenial superstar not
to retire.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My drinking glasses are developing a soap film in my
dishwasher. How can I remove the film and prevent this from
happening again? _Gerald W.
</P>
<P>
   A: You may not be able to remove the film. Some people swear by
regular use of Jet Dry. Denture cleanser often removes film unless
the glass has been etched by mineral deposits. Clean the inside of
the dishwasher with citric-based cleanser (diluted lemon juice).
</P>
<P>
   Wash the filmy glasses in vinegar (add a little to the load). Do
not place utensils or metal objects in the dishwasher with the
glasses. Repeat if necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Upshot/Update/Uproar: The verdict on emu eggs is in from the
American Emu Association-backed study by the Food Protein Research
&AMP; Development Center of Texas A&AMP;M University. The study says an emu
egg has about twice the cholesterol of a chicken egg but it is 10
times the size, weighing about one pound each. You do the math. And
oh, yes, the emu eggshell is green.
</P>
<P>
   Contact Jane Greig at P.O. Box 670, Austin 78767; (512)
445-3697; fax (512) 445-3968.
</P>
<P>
   Jane Greig writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
