   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MERCEDES _ Mercedes-benz announces $40 million expansion of
Alabama sport-utility plant. Will increase production capacity by
10 percent. (Ritzler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIRISK _ Medirisk Inc. shares fell as much as 76 percent after
the provider of computer software to more than 1,000 health-care
companies said second-quarter earnings will miss estimates on weak
sales of database products. Shares fell 13 31/32 to 6 9/32 in
midday trading, after touching 4 7/8, making Medirisk the biggest
percentage decliner in U.S. markets. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   STARBANK _ It's official, Star Banc Corp. will buy Firstar Corp.
of Milwaukee in a $7 billion deal. Pretty much the same-old merger
story except this _ what about reports that HQ will move out of
Cincinnati to Milwaukee? (Townsend, Dayton Daily News). ETA: 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH _ BellSouth has picked Blair Temporaries, a
Maryland-based African-American agency, as one of three companies
receiving a $50 million contract to provide temporary staffing.
(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   CASHPAY _NationsBank is taking on the inner-city, corner
check-cashing place by offering direct deposit and a debit card .
Each transaction costs $1.50. (Chambers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). ETA: 8 p.m.
</P>
