<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-SHORTS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dare to bare in newest short shorts
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL JULY 5: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sixty years ago when Alice Marble stepped onto the court at
Wimbledon wearing shorts, it was a scandalous thing to do. It took
nerve and a sense of the dramatic.
</P>
<P>
   Today, a cheeky group such as the Spice Girls is headline news
in their short shorts. And it still takes some nerve and a good
figure to wiggle into a pair.
</P>
<P>
   This year's crop includes tight shorts threaded with spandex, to
hug well-toned bodies perfectly. Looser styles, in cottons, have
drawstring waists.
</P>
<P>
   Best tops are tubes, tanks and camisoles. For a leggier look,
try platform sandals or thick-soled sneakers. Or go flat with
ballet styles or slides.
</P>
<P>
   A few short tips:
</P>
<P>
   -- Short shorts aren't for everyone. Only wear them if you have
small hips and trim legs.
</P>
<P>
   -- Don't show off too much derriere.
</P>
<P>
   -- Never wear short shorts to the office, even on casual
Fridays. They are strictly leisure wear.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
