u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BANKBOS-PITCHER-BOS &LR;      07-01 0490
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BANKBOS-PITCHER-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BANKBOSTON, SOX' MARTINEZ FIELD COMMUNITY SERVICE AGENCY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By GREGG KRUPA  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Red Sox pitcher Pedro Martinez and BankBoston announced
Wednesday a community service partnership that includes the
establishment of a foundation to provide grants to nonprofit
organizations focused on youth, family and education.
</P>
<P>
   BankBoston will contribute $200,000 to establish the Pedro J.
Martinez and Brother Foundation, and Martinez _ who already does
considerable community service work in his home country, the
Dominican Republic _ will appear on behalf of the bank at some
community events and in a televised public service announcement.
Bank officials said Wednesday that the partnership involves no
commercial appearances or endorsements by Martinez on behalf of the
bank.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez said he will make a decision about how much money he
will contiribute to the foudation after the baseball season is
over.
</P>
<P>
   ``My parents instilled in me and my brothers the need to look
out for others _ not just ourselves,'' Martinez said. ``I recognize
that at times, lots of people feel discouraged by events in their
lives. I wish to reach these people _ especially children _ who
need to know that help is available.''
</P>
<P>
   Martinez's brother Ramon, pitches for the Los Angeles Dodgers,
and another brother, Jesus, is active with both major league
players in community and charitable work in the Dominican Republic.
</P>
<P>
   Chad Gifford, chairman of BankBoston, said that it was Martinez
who approached the bank, but the bank quickly seized upon the idea.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I read about this guy, it was obvious he would serve as
an excellent community resource,'' Gifford said. ``You combine the
best pitcher in baseball with someone who has a wonderful passion
for kids and the public relations sensibility he has, and you look
at what we're trying to do in the community and it's a great idea.
</P>
<P>
   ``But then I met him and for 45 minutes _ as much as I wanted to
talk about baseball _ we talked about kids.''
</P>
<P>
   Bank officials said the demands they will make on Martinez have
little structure, at this point. A televised public service
announcement will feature Martinez highlighting the bank's efforts
to establish mentoring programs in the community. He also is
expected to appear on behalf of the bank during its annual United
Way kickoff day, during which 300 bank employees perform community
service.
</P>
<P>
   Grants from the Pedro J. Martinez and Brothers Foundation will
not be distributed until 1999 to allow time for the trustees to
raise additional funds and to establish clear guidelines for grant
reviews, according to the bank.
</P>
<P>
   For futher information, nonprofit organizations can write to
Franklin Paulino, Pedro J. Martinez and Brothers Foundation, c/o
BankBoston, 100 Federal Street, Mailstop 01-28-05, Boston, MA,
02110.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-01-98 1844EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
