<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: Tampa Bay Devil Rays
 &HT;    ByThomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News SErvice
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 12:35 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Tropicana Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV, radio: Fox Sports South, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Greg Maddux (11-2, 1.64; first
appearance vs. Devils Rays) vs. RHP Jason Johnson (2-5, 5.72; first
appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Maddux, gettin his final start of the first half, is
riding a nine-game win streak, the longest in the league. He has
thrown shutouts in two of his last five starts and in a June 17
complete-game victory over Florida the two runs he gave up were
unearned. Maddux beat Toronto 2-0 on an eight-hitter in his last
start. He leads the NL in ERA (1.64), wins (tied with Tom Glavine
at 11), winning percentage (.846) and shutouts (3) and is second in
innings (137 1/3). He also averages a league-low one walk per nine
innings and has allowed five earned runs in his last 40 innings.
The Devil Rays considered moving Johnson, a 6-foot-6 right-hander,
back one day and letting 10-game-winner Rolando Arrojo face Maddux
but rejected the idea Tuesday. A seventh-round expansion-draft pick
out of the Pirates organization, Johnson will be making his 13th
start and seeks to lower the .304 average he has allowed. Opponents
have 69 hits and 24 walks against him in 48 1/3 innings, and his
5.72 ERA is the highest on Tampa Bay's rotation.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
