</P>
<P>
   BURNED-BOY (Splendora, Texas) _ Investigators say they are all
but convinced that the teen-ager who was named by an 8-year-old
burn victim was with friends and could not have been involved in
the attack. The boy, who was doused with gasoline and burned over
99 percent of his body on his birthday, is in critical condition.
By PAUL McKAY.
</P>
<P>
   OYSTERS-RECALL (Galveston, Texas) _ The number of people
sickened by raw Galveston Bay oysters is fast approaching a
national record, with health officials saying that the number of
victims is 187. That number is expected to climb possibly eclipse
the largest outbreak on record. Last year, 208 people fell ill and
one died in the Northwest after eating raw oysters tainted by the
bacterium Vibrio parahaemolyticus. By KEVIN MORAN. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-CORRUPTION (Laredo, Texas) _ With a former state judge
admitting that he once bribed a prosecutor to fix the outcome of
several drug cases, the district attorney here says he advised his
staff to consider hiring lawyers as a sweeping federal
investigation into corruption continues. By DANE SCHILLER. (Already
filed)
