have a chest transmitter that sends data to a wrist device. In 1998
heart-rate monitor sales in the United States will top $40 million
says Corey Cornacchio, director of marketing at Polar, a company
that claims 80 percent of the worldwide market. (Dan Krauss/New
York Times Photo)
