<P>
   HONGKONG-AIRPORT (Hong Kong) _ When President Jiang Zemin of
China leaves here on Thursday after celebrating the first
anniversary of Hong Kong's handover, he will be the first passenger
to take off from the new $20 billion Hong Kong International
Airport. Unfortunately for Hong Kong, there will be nowhere near as
many people following him as originally planned. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphic clients.)
