<HEADLINE>
FULL SPEED AHEAD FOR SKIP AWAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By JOSEPH DURSO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Skip Away, home from the West with his seven-race winning streak
and his $8.9 million bankroll, was reunited with Sonny Hine
Wednesday at his barn at Belmont Park.
</P>
<P>
   And the trainer indicated with satisfaction that it was full
speed ahead on his itinerary to make Skip Away the richest horse in
racing history.
</P>
<P>
   Skip Away got $600,000 closer to the goal on Sunday in the 34th
start of a grinding four-year career when he outran Puerto Madero
and Gentlemen in the $1 million Hollywood Gold Cup, winning the
acclaim that Hine felt was long owed to his 5-year-old gray.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's been in training for four straight years, and he
overcomes everything,'' Hine said.
</P>
<P>
   The trainer said he was still considering three or four more
races for his superstar, with the prime purpose that of making Skip
Away the first $10 million winner in racing. Cigar holds that
throne at the moment with $9,999,815 million. Skip Away's total is
$8,906,360.
</P>
<P>
   There is some question whether he will return to California for
the $1 million Pacific Classic at Del Mar on Aug. 15, where he
could meet Gentlemen, Puerto Madero and Silver Charm. Hine has also
taken aim at the $500,000 Woodward at Belmont Park on Sept. 19; the
$1 million Jockey Club Gold Cup on Oct. 10 at Belmont, and the $4
million Breeders' Cup Classic at Churchill Downs on Nov. 7.
</P>
</TEXT>
