extent still are, a major environmental problem,'' Dr. de Boer
said.
</P>
<P>
   The research, published in the journal ``Nature,'' also found
brominated compounds in other sea mammals such as harbor seals, but
their presence in sperm whales, which feed exclusively on
deep-water fish, indicates more widespread pollution.
</P>
