<SLUG> BC-BOX-LEWIS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HBO ADDING SIX LEWIS' BOUTS 
</HEADLINE>
 (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Home Box Office announced Wednesday in London that it had
extended Lennox Lewis' contract to six fights, and it also made a
$20 million-plus offer for Evander Holyfield to meet Lewis in a
heavyweight title unification bout in December. But Jim Thomas,
Holyfield's lawyer, said the offer was sleight of hand.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't believe there is any offer,'' Thomas said. ``I believe
it's a media event to divert attention from the fact that they have
locked up Lennox Lewis to fight exclusively on their network, which
has made it harder to do the fight. The competitive forces in the
market can't operate now. We can't take the fight to Showtime, CBS,
ABC or Fox.''
</P>
<P>
   Thomas said he had not received any communication from HBO about
a possible unification bout.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's an attempt to bait or shame Evander into doing
something,'' Thomas said. Holyfield turned down $16 million for a
bout with Lewis last December.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
